      <dsc type="combined">
         <head>Components List</head>
         <c01 level="series">
            <head>Series 1: Business Papers</head>
            <did>
               <unittitle>Business papers, 
               <unitdate type="inclusive">
               1826-1855.</unitdate></unittitle>
               <container label="Folder" type="Folder">1-3</container>
            </did>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Letters, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1826-1839.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">1</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>A few letters, 1826-1832, to Mrs. Sarah T.
                  Nicolson, Middlesex, including one dated 21 October
                  1827, stating the decree for dividing "Rosegill" has
                  been set aside; chiefly letters, 1833-1839, to
                  William K. Perrin of "Goshen," Gloucester County,
                  Virginia from his step-son Robert W. Nicolson,
                  Uniontown, Perry County, Alabama about the management
                  of a cotton plantation.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Letters, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1844-1884.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">2</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>A few business letters, 1844-1849, to Major
                  William K. Perrin but chiefly letters, 1855-1860,
                  from Robert Nicolson in Alabama to Wyndham Kemp in
                  Gloucester County, Virginia about his cotton
                  crop.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Papers relating to the hiring of slaves by
                  William K. Perrin in Gloucester County, Virginia, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">1800-1855,
                  n.d.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">3</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Included are lists of slaves hired out giving
                  names of slaves, masters' names, and amount of
                  transaction, 1800-1806, n.d., receipts for sale of
                  slaves, 1800-1855, and lists of Negroes at Guinea and
                  Fairfield, 1852.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
         </c01>
         <c01 level="series">
            <head>Series 2: Legal Papers</head>
            <did>
               <unittitle>Legal Papers, 
               <unitdate type="inclusive">1723-1895,
               n.d.</unitdate></unittitle>
               <container label="Folder" type="Folder">4-9</container>
            </did>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1723-1812.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <physloc>See also medium oversize file.</physloc>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">4</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Indentures, lists of accounts for William, Willis,
                  Louisa, and Eliza Perrin in the name of John W.
                  Perrin, guardian, 1800-1807.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1820-1829.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">5</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Indentures and receipts of William K. Perrin,
                  George D. Nicolson, and Sarah T. Nicolson.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1830-1847.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">6</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Includes indentures of Sarah T. Nicolson, widow of
                  George D. Nicolson.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1850-1865.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <physloc>See medium oversize file.</physloc>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">7</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Includes agreement, list of debts and receipts of
                  William K. Perrin; last will and testament of William
                  K. Perrin, 16 March 1854 and 25 July 1855; and last
                  will and testament of Willis Perrin, 9 April 1865.
                  Also, Presidential pardon and amnesty granted William
                  K. Perrin for having serves in the Confederate Army,
                  24 August 1865.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  1871-1895.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">8</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Includes indentures and deeds of the descendants
                  of William K. Perrin.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Legal papers, 
                  <unitdate type="inclusive">
                  n.d.</unitdate></unittitle>
                  <container label="Folder" type="Folder">9</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Miscellaneous items.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
         </c01>
